Why can’t Voter ID be in the special
election?
We can't put them on the same ballot because they are
using two different avenues to change California law. This
upcoming special election is a
legislative constitutional amendment that the state
legislature can trigger with a 2/3 majority vote; that then
sends it to the citizens to vote on the amendment. Our
Voter ID initiative is a citizen's constitutional amendment
which requires getting a number of signatures equivalent
to 8% of the previous election's recorded votes for the
gubernatorial race, which in this case is ~850,000
signatures. Once we collect these, the Secretary of State
confirms the signatures which then triggers it to be on the
ballot for consideration at the next election. Hope this
makes sense, feel free to reach out with further questions.
